<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,325,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,325,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi" box="[445,621,325,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refString="Endrodi, S. (1985) The Dynastinae of the World. Dr W. Junk, Dordrecht, The Netherlands. 800 p." type="book" year="1985">
Endrödi (
<number box="[555,613,325,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[632,927,325,350]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Hylobothyus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis box="[632,927,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Hylobothyus columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1104,325,350]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Hylobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[989,1104,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">H. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated by the absence of a pronotal basal margin in the former, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[859,971,361,386]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Hylobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[859,971,361,386]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">H. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotum is strongly bordered at its base. Furthermore, the 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyen, 1834" authorityName="Meyen" authorityYear="1834" box="[417,524,397,422]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Pygidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">pygidium</taxonomicName>
is strongly punctate in 
<taxonomicName box="[797,977,397,422]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Hylobothyus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis box="[797,977,397,422]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">H. columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and nearly smooth in the other species. The parameres of 
<taxonomicName box="[354,531,433,458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Hylobothyus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis box="[354,531,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">H. columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are longer and narrower (
<figureCitation box="[821,956,433,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,889,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,878,1643]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Hylobothynus columbianus (holotype): 40) habitus in dorsal view, 41) parameres in frontal view, 42) parameres in lateral view, 43) maxillary apical palpomere, 44) habitus in lateral view. Hylobothynus obesus (holotype): 45) habitus in dorsal view, 46) parameres in frontal view, 47) parameres in lateral view, 48) locality records of Hylobothynus in Colombia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234028/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
Figs. 
<number box="[885,956,433,457]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="41.5" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="41.0">41–42</number>
</figureCitation>
) than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1123,1233,433,458]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Hylobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1233,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">H. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1248,1386,433,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,889,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,878,1643]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Hylobothynus columbianus (holotype): 40) habitus in dorsal view, 41) parameres in frontal view, 42) parameres in lateral view, 43) maxillary apical palpomere, 44) habitus in lateral view. Hylobothynus obesus (holotype): 45) habitus in dorsal view, 46) parameres in frontal view, 47) parameres in lateral view, 48) locality records of Hylobothynus in Colombia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234028/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
Figs. 
<number box="[1312,1386,433,458]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="46.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="46.0">46–47</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,400,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Locality records.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[416,497,469,494]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,889,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,878,1643]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 48. Hylobothynus columbianus (holotype): 40) habitus in dorsal view, 41) parameres in frontal view, 42) parameres in lateral view, 43) maxillary apical palpomere, 44) habitus in lateral view. Hylobothynus obesus (holotype): 45) habitus in dorsal view, 46) parameres in frontal view, 47) parameres in lateral view, 48) locality records of Hylobothynus in Colombia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234028/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
Fig. 
<number box="[468,497,470,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<typeStatus box="[512,619,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCount box="[631,668,470,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="generic">
<number box="[631,643,470,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1.0">1</number>
♂
</specimenCount>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[680,852,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
Putumayo (
<number box="[820,835,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1.0">1</number>
):
</emphasis>
Mocoa, 
<quantity box="[950,1023,469,494]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" unit="m" value="530.0">530 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[1035,1116,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1921-02">
ii. 
<number box="[1056,1116,469,494]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</date>
, Werner Hopp [
<collectionCode box="[1292,1383,470,493]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/99a5-d0z2" name="Zoologisches Museum der Humboldt Universitaet" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">ZMHU</collectionCode>
]. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,469,505,530]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi" box="[484,640,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refString="Endrodi, S. (1969) Monographie der Dynastinae. 4. Tribus: Pentodontini (Coleoptera, Lamellicornia). Entomologische Abhandlungen Museum fur Tierkunde, Dresden, 37, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1969">
Endrödi 
<number box="[583,640,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[703,754,506,529]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dechambre" box="[768,966,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. (1979) Nouveaux Dynastidae Pentodontini americains (Coleoptera Scarabaeoidea). Revue francaise d´entomologie (N. S.), 1, 101 - 105." type="journal article" year="1979">
Dechambre 
<number box="[906,966,505,529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe" box="[977,1142,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refString="Ratcliffe, B. C. (1981) The fourth Hylobothynus: spanning the Amazonian gap (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Dynastinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 35, 303 - 306." type="journal article" year="1981">
Ratcliffe 
<number box="[1082,1142,505,529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,325,566]" box="[199,1092,541,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,541,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Natural history.</emphasis>
